PART 1: FUNDAMENTAL CONCEPTS
=============================

WHAT IS ARTIFICIAL INTELLIGENCE (AI)?
====================================

Definition:
----------
AI systems are computer programs that can learn and make decisions independently
without human intervention.

Key Characteristics:
-------------------
• Learning capability from data
• Autonomous decision-making
• Pattern recognition
• Problem-solving abilities

Role of Code in AI:
------------------
• Code provides instructions to AI systems
• Without code, AI cannot function
• Code is the foundation that enables AI operations
• All AI systems require programming to operate

---

WHAT IS GENERATIVE AI?
======================

Definition:
----------
Generative AI is a subfield of Artificial Intelligence that focuses on creating
new content, rather than just analyzing or classifying existing data.

Position in AI Hierarchy:
------------------------
AI (Broad Field)
├── Machine Learning
│   ├── Deep Learning
│   │   ├── Neural Networks
│   │   └── Generative AI ← Our Focus
│   └── Traditional ML
└── Other AI Subfields

Key Capabilities:
----------------
• Text generation (articles, stories, code)
• Image creation and manipulation
• Audio synthesis
• Video generation
• Music composition
• Design creation

Common Examples:
---------------
• ChatGPT, Claude (Text Generation)
• DALL-E, Midjourney (Image Generation)
• GitHub Copilot (Code Generation)
• Suno AI (Music Generation)

---

WHAT IS AGENTIC AI?
===================

Definition:
----------
Agentic AI refers to AI systems that can act autonomously, make decisions, and
take actions to achieve specific goals without direct human control for each step.

Key Characteristics of Agentic AI:
----------------------------------
• Autonomy: Operates independently
• Goal-oriented: Works toward specific objectives
• Decision-making: Makes choices without human intervention
• Action-taking: Executes tasks in the real or digital world
• Planning: Can create and execute multi-step plans

Agentic AI vs. Generative AI:
-----------------------------
Generative AI: Creates content when prompted
Agentic AI: Takes initiative and acts to achieve goals

Example Comparison:
------------------
Generative AI: "Write a blog post about climate change" → Creates text
Agentic AI: "Increase our social media engagement" → Creates posts, analyzes results, 
            adjusts strategy, posts content, monitors performance

Real-World Applications:
-----------------------
• Autonomous vehicles
• Personal AI assistants
• Trading bots
• Customer service agents
• Research assistants

